Description: 2006 Schecter Raider 6-string electric guitar, in good condition. Kind of a rare item, I believe these were only made for one year, and only offered through Guitar Center... that's what I believe to be true. I guess the eye catching feature of his guitar is the inlays. Crossbones inlays with a skull and crossbones at the 12th fret. Kind of unique. Active Duncan Design humbuckers, 3-way pickup selector switch, 1 volume 1 tone control. The electronics work as they should. An overall good condition structurally. No cracks or breaks anywhere. The paint is mostly glossing, though it has lost a little gloss here and there, especially on top. Some of the paint has worn off around the edges. Not unattractive at all though. A few minor nicks and dings. Just looks like it's been played some. The other eye-catching feature of this listing is the cat eating in the background behind picture number one. That's a stray that wandered up into the yard, and we've been feeding him for about a year now. Feel free to make a separate offer on the cat. I will find a gig bag for it (the guitar), it didn't come with one, but I've got some laying around.
